  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_1' aria-label=\" Sadiq B. Hanchinmani versus The State of Karnataka & Ors. R1: The State of Karnataka R2: Chndrumal R3: Sanjay R4: Nandkumar R5: Vijay pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('1','2025','2025_11_246_263','2025INSC1282'); ><font size='4'> <strong>SADIQ B. HANCHINMANI<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>THE STATE OF KARNATAKA & ORS. R1: THE STATE OF KARNATAKA R2: CHNDRUMAL R3: SANJAY R4: NANDKUMAR R5: VIJAY </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 11 S.C.R. 246</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 1282</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010005682025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : PANKAJ MITHAL<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, AHSANUDDIN AMANULLAH</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Issue arose whether the direction for investigation to the police issued by the JMFC-Judicial Magistrate First Class u/s.156(3) CrPC which was quashed by the impugned orders, justified; had sufficient material before it so as to justify the course of action of referring the matter for investigation to the police invoking power u/s.156(3) of the Code, resulting in the institution of the FIR. Headnotes&dagger; Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 &ndash; ss.156(3), 482 &ndash;<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 04-11-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CRIMINAL APPEAL No. 4728/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Appeal(s) allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('1','2025','2025_11_246_263','2025IN